---
title: Organic Beef Meatloaf Parm over Spaghetti Marinara
description: Chicken Parm, Veal Parm, Meatball Parm… Pork Meatloaf Parm? Yes, dreams really do come true. Our chefs have Parm-ified individual pork meatloaves, layering them with mouthwatering marinara sauce and a cheesy panko topping. They’re baked until the meat is perfectly tender and the crust is crispy and melty, then served over spaghetti marinara with a sprinkle of more cheese for good measure. Parm-fection? We think so.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/640748285680106c2a0d7f83-2d90b2c3.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64a5ae4e3e9315263c4e357c.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 1050 kcal
  fat: 51 g
  saturated fat: 19 g
  carbohydrates: 94 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 52 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1700 mg
servings: 2
cuisine: Italian
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/organic-beef-meatloaf-parm-64a5ae4e3e9315263c4e357c
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a large pot of
@water{}(salted) to a boil.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup},
and a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}; season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @organic ground beef{10%ounce}, half the panko
mixture, half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}, and 1 TBSP water; season
generously with salt (we used ½ tsp) and pepper.

> Swap in pork or organic beef for this ground beef if you prefer.

Form pork mixture into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4); flatten tops.
Place on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}.

Evenly spread tops of meatloaves with 1 TBSP @marinara{5%ounce cup} each (you'll
use the rest later). Mound with remaining panko mixture, pressing gently to
adhere.

Bake meatloaves on top rack until pork is cooked through and crust is browned
and crispy, ~{22-28%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve ¾ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Heat #pot{} used for pasta over medium-high heat. Add reserved pasta cooking
water, @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, remaining
marinara, remaining Tuscan Heat Spice, @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{1/2%tsp},
and @sugar{1.5%tsp}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook until
slightly thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> Reserve pasta water is important for loosening the sauce to your desired
> consistency.

Stir drained spaghetti, half the @parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, and
@butter{1%tablespoon} into pot with sauce. Season generously with salt and
pepper.

Divide pasta between plates and top with meatloaves. (TIP: If you prefer, serve
meatloaves on the side instead.) Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan and serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.